        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): clear admin scopes for backend self-pairing",
        "body": "Summary\n- Stop treating shared token/password auth as sufficient to preserve any self-declared operator scopes for local backend self-pairing.\n- Keep unscoped backend local handoff intact, while routing scoped local backend Gateway calls through normal device identity so internal loopback calls still work.\n- Add explicit issue coverage for loopback/no-Origin backend identity + shared token/password + self-declared operator scopes + no device identity.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** Device-less local/shared-secret backend Gateway clients must not preserve self-declared operator scopes while skipping pairing.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Temporary local OpenClaw Gateway from this PR branch, token auth, loopback WebSocket at `ws://127.0.0.1:39139`, channels skipped, configured via a temporary `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR` and `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH`.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Started the local Gateway from this branch, then ran a Node/tsx WebSocket client using `GatewayClient` as `gateway-client` / `backend` with shared token auth, `deviceIdentity: null`, and `scopes: [\"operator.write\"]`. The client then attempted `sessions.list`.\n\n**Evidence after fix:** Terminal output from the live local Gateway client:\n\n```text\n$ OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=/tmp/openclaw-pr86192-proof-... \\\n  OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-pr86192-proof-.../openclaw.json \\\n  OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PORT=39139 \\\n  OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=secret \\\n  node --import tsx --input-type=module\n\nlocal gateway: ws://127.0.0.1:39139\nbackend shared-token no-device requested scopes: [operator.write]\nhello auth scopes: []\nsessions.list error: missing scope: operator.read\n```\n\nGateway runtime log excerpt for the same live connection:\n\n```text\n[ws] ⇄ res ✗ sessions.list 1ms errorCode=INVALID_REQUEST errorMessage=missing scope: operator.read\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** The backend shared-token, no-device connection completed, but the server returned no authorized scopes in `hello-ok`; the follow-up read-scoped RPC failed with `missing scope: operator.read`. This verifies that non-admin self-declared scopes are cleared too, not only `operator.admin`.\n\n**What was not tested:** Remote browser-origin behavior was not live-tested here; focused regression coverage covers the local and shared-secret-loopback cases changed by this PR.\n\nAdditional verification\n```text\n$ pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.gateway.config.ts src/gateway/call.test.ts src/gateway/server/ws-connection/handshake-auth-helpers.test.ts src/gateway/server.auth.compat-baseline.test.ts src/gateway/server.auth.control-ui.test.ts\n\nTest Files  4 passed (4)\nTests  165 passed (165)\n\n$ pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.gateway-server.config.ts src/gateway/server.sessions-send.test.ts\n\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  3 passed (3)\n\n$ pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.agents.config.ts src/agents/code-mode.test.ts\n\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  30 passed (30)\n\n$ git diff --check\n# no output\n```\n\nFixes openclaw/openclaw#72418\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-72418",
